$rthem is visualization of high-dimensional data sets. The main goal of data visualization is to find a$\backslash$rone, two or three-dimensional descriptive data projection, which captures and highlights important$\backslash$rknowledge about data while eliminating the information loss. This process helps people to explore$\backslash$rand understand the data structure that facilitates the choice of a proper method for the data analysis,$\backslash$re.g., selecting simple or complex classifier etc. The application of LLE for visualization is described$\backslash$rin this research.$\backslash$rThe benefits of dimensionality reduction are commonly used in obtaining compact data$\backslash$rrepresentation before applying a classifier. In this case, the main goal is to obtain a low-dimensional$\backslash$rdata representation, which possesses good class separability. For this purpose, a supervised variant of$\backslash$rLLE (SLLE) is proposed in this thesis.},
